  <summary>2/13/2001--Introduced.
Comprehensive Insurance Coverage of Childhood Immunization Act of 2001 - Amends the Public Health Service Act and the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974 to require comprehensive health insurance coverage for childhood immunization to be provided by health plans and insurance issuers in both group and individual markets.</summary>
